        <span class="style17">WELCOME TO ICL COLLEGE!!! &nbsp;</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="style9">
&nbsp;<span class="style16">DISCIPLINE AND CODE OF CONDUCT :</span></p>
    <p class="style15">
        Self-discipline is the best discipline. All the students are expected to observe 
        rules and regulations currently in force to enable smooth working of the 
        college. Students shall not do anything inside or outside the college that will 
        interfere with the administration or hamper the image of the college. No outside 
        influence, political or otherwise will be tolerated. Ragging and Smoking in the 
        college premises and in the canteen is strictly prohibited. Students should 
        always display their valid college identity card while in the college premises. 
        Students must not loiter in the college corridors when lectures/ 
        tutorials/examinations and tests are in progress. Use of mobile phones is 
        strictly prohibited in the college premises. Students must carry valid identity 
        card while representing the college at any other place and their behavior should 
        not damage the image of the college. Picnics and excursions or trips cannot be 
        organized by students without the written permission of the Principal. 
        Attendance for seminars/ guest lectures and counseling sessions are mandatory 
        for all students. Students are required to dress decently keeping in mind the 
        decorum of an educational institution. In all matters relating to admission, 
        attendance, discipline, granting of facilities, conduct of extra curricular 
        activities, granting of examination forms, etc., the decision of the Principal 
        shall be final &amp; binding on all the students. </p>
<p class="style13">
        ATTENDANCE &amp; GRANT OF TERMS:</p>
    <p class="style18">
        Attendance of students is regulated by 0.119 &amp; 0.125 0.119 : As per the 
        circulation no. VA/235/98 dated 03/07/1998 related to 0.119 for granting of 
        terms, attendance of 75% of theory, practical &amp; tutorials (wherever prescribed) 
        separately will be required, out of the total number of lectures, practicals &amp; 
        tutorials conducted in the term. 0.125 : As per this ordinance, to keep a term 
        at a college or recognised institution, an under graduate must complete to the 
        satisfaction of the Principal or the Head of the Institution, the course of 
        study at the college or Institution prescribed for such terms for the class to 
        which such undergraduates belong. Parents are advised to take note of above 
        mandatory ordinances of maintaining minimum attendance. Application for leave of 
        absence of their wards on account of illness or any other valid reason should be 
        submitted along with the proof to the college authorities within two days of 
        resuming classes. Parents are requested to attend the term-end counseling 
        sessions to keep themselves abreast of their wards attendance and progress. 
        </p>
